    <!-- III. Strategic Project Concepts: Applying MarinaChain's Technology -->
    <h2>III. Strategic Project Concepts: Applying MarinaChain's Technology</h2>
    <p>This section illustrates how MarinaChain’s core technology (MarinaNet, ParseAI, AI-driven analytics) translates into fundable project concepts for the top 2 opportunities (MarinaChain as key partner).</p>

    <!-- Concept 1 - AI-GREEN PORT -->
    <div class="simplified-concept-card">
        <h3>1. AI-GREEN PORT: AI-Driven Decarbonisation for Energy-Intensive Ports</h3>
        <span class="mapped-to">Mapped to: HORIZON-CL4-2026-CLEAN-INDUSTRY-01-01 (Innovation Action) - Decarbonisation of Energy-Intensive Industries</span>
        <span class="estimated-funding">MarinaChain Estimated Funding Share: <strong>€1.5M - €3.0M</strong></span>
        
        <p><strong>Concept Essence:</strong> To deploy and validate MarinaChain's **AI platform** across three major European ports and their industrial ecosystems. The project will automate and optimize **carbon lifecycle accounting** and energy use for both visiting vessels and shoreside industrial operations, creating a replicable "Green Port" model.</p>

        <p><strong>MarinaChain's Partner Contribution:</strong> MarinaChain will lead the digitalization work package, focusing on integrating their AI-driven emission compliance tools to achieve **full transparency** of GHG emissions across the port ecosystem. This input is critical for establishing the **digital backbone** for the new Green Port model and providing auditable data for regulatory compliance.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Strategic Rationale:</strong> Directly addresses the call's aim to decarbonize heavy industry using digital tools. This project positions MarinaChain as a key enabler for the green transition of Europe's most critical infrastructure, showcasing a powerful **B2G (Business-to-Government/Port Authority)** and **B2B** solution.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Concept 2 - SEA-SENTINEL -->
    <div class="simplified-concept-card">
        <h3>2. SEA-SENTINEL: Predictive Analytics for Maritime Supply Chain Resilience</h3>
        <span class="mapped-to">Mapped to: HORIZON-CL4-2026-RESILIENCE-01-01 (RIA) - Resilient Supply Chain Monitoring & Analytics</span>
        <span class="estimated-funding">MarinaChain Estimated Funding Share: <strong>€1.0M - €2.0M</strong></span>
        
        <p><strong>Concept Essence:</strong> To enhance MarinaChain's data platform with a **predictive analytics module** capable of anticipating and mitigating disruptions in the maritime supply chain. The system will process diverse data sets (shipping data, port congestion, weather, geopolitical risk) to provide **actionable resilience intelligence**.</p>

        <p><strong>MarinaChain's Partner Contribution:</strong> MarinaChain will provide the core **data processing and AI modelling capacity**. The focus will be on developing and validating the proprietary **ParseAI engine** to predict key risk indicators (KRIs) that impact supply chain flow and cost efficiency, ensuring the system is transparent and reliable for complex decision-making.</p>
        
        <p><strong>Strategic Rationale:</strong> Aligns perfectly with the call's focus on strengthening EU strategic autonomy by making critical supply chains more resilient. It expands MarinaChain's value proposition from emissions compliance to crucial **operational and economic resilience**, a high-value service for logistics firms and governments.</p>
    </div>

